/-! #### The word-coupled head-start family (the F1 (4/5)/(5/5) fix carrier)

`paper3HeadlineSolFamNW wg` is the `paper3HeadlineSolFamN` sibling at the
word-coupled clock scale `bgpScaleW wg = bgpScale·6^(inputLenU 1 wg + 220)`
(params `bgpParamsNW wg = (cμ, cα) = (1000, 300)·bgpScaleW wg`, warm gain
`paper3WarmGainQNW wg`).  This is the IMPLEMENTABLE form of the "clock head
start" fix for the F1 (4/5)/(5/5) falsity (see the design verdict in
`BGPParamsN.lean`):

* `μ(0) = μ₀(w) > 0` (RUN_LOG option (a) literally) is IMPOSSIBLE — the gate
  coordinates would need transcendental initial values `e^{−μ₀/2}`, breaking
  the rational-PIVP `encoder_presented` obligation;
* per-word rates as FIELD coefficients (option (b) literally) are ILLEGAL —
  the final `EventualThresholdSimulation` fixes ONE field, `w` enters only
  through the (computably presented, rational) initial condition;
* word-coupled homogeneous clock SPEED-UP is both: at the analytic layer it
  is the params family `bgpParamsNW wg` below (this file); at the final
  PIVP-realization layer `cμ`/`cα` become constant coordinates
  (derivative `0`) with `w`-dependent rational inits — exactly the existing
  warm-gain-coordinate pattern, field unchanged.  `μ(t) = 1000·bgpScaleW·t`
  delivers any `w`-linear head-start value inside `[0, ε]`: on `[0, π/6]`
  the u-kernel mass is `≤ 1/(200·bgpScaleW wg)`, which beats the F1 depth
  weight `6^{inputLenU+O(1)}` against the rate-INDEPENDENT `O(bgpScale·e^{199})`
  hull boxes (`bgpScaleW_beats_depth_weight`), making the F1-NW inputs
  (4/5)/(5/5) TRUE on the diagonal. -/

