/-- **Crude inter-read `|mix − z|` box** (part 1 of the mixture-box
discharge): conditional on the cycle-`j` boundary tube and window envelope,
`|mix − z| ≤ paper3F1MixCrudeBoxNW` on the whole `[wr j, zOffEnd j]`.
Segment `[wr j, zOffStart j]`: the maintained u-tube pins the branch hull
(`|mix| ≤ 2·D_U`) and `z` is relaxation-trapped in the hull of its
`Cwin`-sized read entry.  Segment `[zOffStart j, zOffEnd j]` (`sin ≤ 0`):
first-exit — were `z` to move by `1`, the `e^{−200·bgpScaleW·τ}`-suppressed
z-gate would have to carry a `MixCrudeBox`-sized source, which the freeze
kill forbids; inside the box the u-relaxation and the affine branch hull
reproduce the `MixCrudeBox` bound. -/
