/-- **No-slop prewrite `z−u` hold on `[zOffEnd j, ws (j+1)]`.**  The pair
error `φ = z − u` satisfies
`φ' = −(kZ + kU)·φ + kZ·(mix − u) = (kZ + kU)·(target − φ)` with the
relaxation target `kZ·(mix − u)/(kZ + kU)` bounded by the prewrite mix box
`B` (both kernels are positive).  Scalar trapping gives
`|φ(ws (j+1))| ≤ max E B` with NO additive slop: the ctrl-jump pre-write
(the z-gate genuinely reopens on this tail — the reason the retimed source
